                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.01/517: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul on Special Detail at Chita</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thomas</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chita</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-11-15T10:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 15, 1922—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 19—3:06 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>On November 14 after speeches in the popular assembly in favor of union with
                    Soviet Russia the Government of the Far Eastern Republic renounced its power.
                    The popular assembly then unanimously passed a law to repeal the constitution of
                    the Far Eastern Republic, to dissolve the popular assembly, to appoint a
                    revolutionary committee to take over the power, and to apply to Moscow to be
                    taken in as an integral part of Soviet Russia. A revolutionary committee was
                    elected of which Kobozeff is President and Janson a member.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thomas</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
